--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Bytes Format Units Label   Explanations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   1-  5  F5.3   ---  phase   Template light curve phase
   7- 11  F5.3   ---  value   Template value
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

================================================================================



J/ApJ/708/717       Light curve templates of RR Lyrae stars       (Sesar+, 2010)
================================================================================
Light curve templates and Galactic distribution of RR Lyrae stars from Sloan
Digital Sky Survey stripe 82.
    Sesar B., Ivezic Z., Grammer S.H., Morgan D.P., Becker A.C., Juric M.,
    De Lee N., Annis J., Beers T.C., Fan X., Lupton R.H., Gunn J.E.,
    Knapp G.R., Jiang L., Jester S., Johnston D.E., Lampeitl H.
   <Astrophys. J., 708, 717-741 (2010)>
   =2010ApJ...708..717S
================================================================================
ADC_Keywords: Photometry, SDSS ; Stars, variable ; Stars, halo
Keywords: Galaxy: halo - Galaxy: stellar content - Galaxy: structure -
          methods: data analysis - stars: horizontal-branch -
          stars: statistics - stars: variables: other

Abstract:
    We present an improved analysis of halo substructure traced by RR
    Lyrae stars in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey (SDSS) stripe 82 region.
    With the addition of SDSS-II data, a revised selection method based on
    new ugriz light curve templates results in a sample of 483 RR Lyrae
    stars that is essentially free of contamination. The main result from
    our first study persists: the spatial distribution of halo stars at
    galactocentric distances 5-100kpc is highly inhomogeneous. At least
    20% of halo stars within 30kpc from the Galactic center can be
    statistically associated with substructure. We present strong direct
    evidence, based on both RR Lyrae stars and main-sequence stars, that
    the halo stellar number density profile significantly steepens beyond
    a Galactocentric distance of ~30kpc, and a larger fraction of the
    stars are associated with substructure. By using a novel method that
    simultaneously combines data for RR Lyrae and main-sequence stars, and
    using photometric metallicity estimates for main-sequence stars
    derived from deep co-added u-band data, we measure the metallicity of
    the Sagittarius dSph tidal stream (trailing arm) toward RA~2h-3h
    and DE~0{deg} to be 0.3dex higher ([Fe/H]=-1.2) than that of
    surrounding halo field stars.

Description:
    We have combined SDSS-I imaging runs used in Sesar et al.
    (2007AJ....134.2236S) with recalibrated SDSS-II SN (Frieman et al.
    2008AJ....135..338F) imaging runs, and created a catalog with ~4.4
    million unique unresolved (point source) objects. Each object in the
    catalog was observed at least four times in the ugr bands. We selected
    483 RR Lyrae stars in SDSS stripe 82.

File Summary:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 FileName   Lrecl  Records   Explanations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ReadMe         80        .   This file
table2.dat    295      483   Light curve parameters for stripe 82 RR Lyrae stars
table3.dat    115      483   Positions and derived parameters of stripe 82
                             RR Lyrae stars
phot/*          .      483  *Position and ugriz photometry for each star
templ/*         .       98  *Individual files for ugriz RR Lyrae template
                             light curves
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes on phot/*: This directory contains positions and ugriz photometry
  for 483 stripe 82 RR Lyrae stars. The filenames correspond to RR Lyrae ID
  numbers in Tables 2 and 3.
Notes on templ/*: This directory contains ugriz RR Lyrae template light
  curves. The number in the filename corresponds to the template ID in 
  Table 2 and the letter identifies the band.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

